  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nDoing some experiments (manually managing nonces) with web3j and geth (Rinkeby) when I noticed the following:\r\nGiven the next valid nonce is 3, then:\r\n- Submit a transaction with nonce 3 => Mined successfully \r\n- Submit a transaction with nonce 5 => Tx is in txpool.pending\r\n- Submit a transaction with nonce 4 => Mined successfully\r\nIf I understand correctly, the tx with nonce 5 should be picked up automatically because the nonce gap was closed, yet this transaction stays in txpool.pending.\r\n\r\nNot 100% sure this is expected behavior.\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.7.3-stable on Ubuntu 16.04\r\n\r\n",
